cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper deals with a security issue in wireless communication systems, specifically in the pilot training phase. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the impact of the attack on the quality of transmission, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The proposed algorithm involves channel estimation, which is a common topic in cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a secure transmission scheme, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves simulation results, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
